docs.lead_paragraph: Opening the mouth to feed is an important element of nursing, an instinct fetuses develop in the womb.

headline.main: A Feeding Instinct Starts in the Womb
headline.print_headline: Human Behavior: A Feeding Instinct Starts in the Womb

docs.abstract: Study in journal Developmental Psychology finds that fetuses begin to teach themselves anticipation of touch, skill used in feeding after birth, by touching their own heads and mouths while in utero; study suggests that premature babies may not have fully developed skill.
docs.snippet: Opening the mouth to feed is an important element of nursing, an instinct fetuses develop in the womb.
